00:46:52.580 --> 00:46:58.240
So, OpenPlay consists of three
different API layers.

00:46:58.290 --> 00:47:02.000
There's a game interface,
which is the easiest to use.

00:47:02.000 --> 00:47:04.370
It just takes a couple minutes
to get something up and running.

00:47:04.380 --> 00:47:07.920
That is the old NetSprocket API.

00:47:07.920 --> 00:47:13.350
There's the protocol interface,
which is basically a good wrapper

00:47:13.640 --> 00:47:15.880
around the low-level APIs.

00:47:15.880 --> 00:47:19.640
This is the old OpenPlay interface.

00:47:21.120 --> 00:47:22.820
And then there's the
networking interface,

00:47:22.820 --> 00:47:28.940
and these are the net module
wrappers around TCP/IP and AppleTalk.

00:47:28.940 --> 00:47:32.870
And that's what gives you
your protocol independence.

00:47:34.990 --> 00:47:38.100
